Analysis of the Target Structure
--------------------------------
From the picture, the model actually consists of two separate sub‐assemblies:

1) A “three‐arch” arrangement on the left (12 total blocks):  
   • Base Layer: Three red arches in a row.  
   • Top/Front Layer:  
     – One blue cube sitting on the left arch.  
     – Two yellow half‐cylinders bridging the tops of the arches (one spanning the left/middle arches, the other spanning the middle/right arches).  
     – One orange cube on top of the right arch.  
   • Rear Layer (behind the arches):  
     – Left Arch: one short green rectangular block plus one tall yellow rectangular block behind it.  
     – Middle Arch: one tall green rectangular block plus one tall yellow rectangular block behind it.  
     – Right Arch: one short green rectangular block behind it.  

2) A “ring” assembly on the right (5 total blocks):  
   • Four red corner‐arc blocks arranged to form a circular opening when viewed from the front.  
   • One short green rectangular block passing horizontally through the ring (“green band”).  

Required Blocks and Their Dictionary Indices
--------------------------------------------
Below is the complete parts‐list, keyed to the block‐dictionary indices (re‐using indices as needed without re‐orienting any block).

A) Left‐Side “Three‐Arch” Structure (12 blocks)
  1. Red Arch (#1) – three copies  
  2. Blue Cube (#5) – one copy  
  3. Orange Cube (#6) – one copy  
  4. Yellow Half‐Cylinder (#13) – two copies  
  5. Short Green Rectangular Block (#10) – two copies  
  6. Tall Green Rectangular Block (#8) – one copy  
  7. Tall Yellow Rectangular Block (#11) – two copies  

B) Right‐Side “Ring” Structure (5 blocks)
  1. Red Corner‐Arc (#2) – two copies  
  2. Red Corner‐Arc (mirror) (#3) – two copies  
  3. Short Green Rectangular Block (#7) – one copy  

Step‐by‐Step Assembly Order
---------------------------
{  
  Step1:  Move block with index 1   (red arch)  
  Step2:  Move block with index 1   (red arch)  
  Step3:  Move block with index 1   (red arch)  
  Step4:  Move block with index 5   (blue cube)  
  Step5:  Move block with index 13  (yellow half‐cylinder)  
  Step6:  Move block with index 13  (yellow half‐cylinder)  
  Step7:  Move block with index 6   (orange cube)  
  Step8:  Move block with index 10  (short green rectangular, behind left arch)  
  Step9:  Move block with index 11  (tall yellow rectangular, behind left arch)  
  Step10: Move block with index 8   (tall green rectangular, behind middle arch)  
  Step11: Move block with index 11  (tall yellow rectangular, behind middle arch)  
  Step12: Move block with index 10  (short green rectangular, behind right arch)  
  Step13: Move block with index 2   (red corner‐arc for ring)  
  Step14: Move block with index 2   (red corner‐arc for ring)  
  Step15: Move block with index 3   (red corner‐arc for ring)  
  Step16: Move block with index 3   (red corner‐arc for ring)  
  Step17: Move block with index 7   (short green rectangular “band” through ring)  
}
